  "description": "Free verse is poetry written without a fixed [meter](./meter.md) or [rhyme](./rhyme.md) scheme. The term translates the French *vers libre*, which named the movement that emerged in late-nineteenth-century French poetry and was taken up in English by Pound, Eliot, Williams, and others in the early twentieth century.",
